  Visual Storytelling 101 (Part 1)

In this video, we'll take a look at how filmmakers tell stories. If you are new to the world of filmmaking, this is a SUPER helpful video to watch. If you are more experienced, I would totally understand if you want to skip.

This Video Will Cover:

  • Storytelling Concepts
  • Cinematic Shot Styles
  • Framing

You can also download the PDF guide to follow along with this presentation below. Note: Part 2 will continue in the next module.

Important: Watch the Video Below Before Proceeding to the Next Module

Further Resources for Learning Storytelling

  • Story: Substance, Structure, Style and the Principles of Screenwriting by Robert McKee - A comprehensive guide to the art and craft of screenwriting.
  • Save the Cat! - One of the most popular books ever written on screenwriting.
  • The Hero with a Thousand Faces by Joseph Campbell - A classic study of the hero's journey, a common narrative structure in storytelling.
  • Story Genius by Lisa Cron - A guide to writing stories that are both original and emotionally resonant.
  • The Anatomy of Story by John Truby - A comprehensive guide to the structure of stories.
  • The Writer's Journey by Christopher Vogler - A guide to the hero's journey, adapted from Joseph Campbell's work.

YouTube Channels for Dissecting Films

  • Lessons from the Screenplay - A channel that analyzes the storytelling techniques of popular films.
  • Nerdwriter1 - A channel that explores a variety of topics related to film, including storytelling.
  • The Take - A channel that analyzes the storytelling techniques of popular films and TV shows.
  • Now You See It - A channel that explores the hidden meanings and symbolism in popular films.
  • Every Frame a Painting - One of the best film analysis channels ever made. Discover the hidden storytelling strategies in your favorite films.
